The electrostatic energy of a point charge \( q \) at the center of a conducting spherical shell is derived from the energy stored in the electric field between the inner radius \( r_1 \) and outer radius \( r_2 \), yielding the form \(\frac{1}{2} \frac{q^2}{4\pi\epsilon_0} \left( \frac{1}{r_1} - \frac{1}{r_2} \right)\).

\boxed{D}
